# Privacy Policy

Last Updated: July 2026

## Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how this Discord bot Furina collects, uses, stores, and protects information while operating on Discord.

## Information We Collect

The Bot may process the following information:

- Discord User IDs
- Discord Server IDs
- Discord Channel IDs
- Discord Role IDs
- Discord Message IDs
- Moderation records (warnings, temporary punishments, moderation logs)
- Reminder data created by users
- Server configuration settings
- Presence information when required for enabled features
- Message content only when required for bot functionality

The Bot does not collect passwords, email addresses, payment information, or other sensitive personal information.

## How Information Is Used

Information is processed only to provide bot features including:

- Moderation
- Role management
- Anti-spam protection
- AFK system
- Reminder system
- Logging
- Utility commands
- Presence statistics
- Interactive commands

## Message Content

Message content is only processed when necessary for features such as:

- Anti-spam detection
- AFK detection
- Command handling
- Interactive bot responses

Message content is never sold or shared with third parties.

## Data Storage

Only information necessary for bot functionality is stored.

Stored data may include:

- Moderation logs
- Warnings
- Reminder entries
- Server configuration
- Temporary role information

## AI and Machine Learning

User data and message content are **not** used to train artificial intelligence or machine learning models.

## Data Sharing

The Bot does not sell or share user data with third parties except where required by law.

## Data Removal

Server administrators may remove server-related configuration by removing the Bot from their server.

Users may request deletion of stored personal data by contacting the bot developer.

## Contact

For questions regarding this Privacy Policy, contact the bot developer through the official support server.
